name: Kew Ong Yah Temple (Upper Serangoon) l 国家古迹 l 百年古庙 l 后港斗母宫 l

reviews.text: Surprised to find this 100+ year old temple here in the heartlands as not many old buildings get to be preserved in the neighbourhoods. Lots of heritage value and beautiful stories behind this temple. Tonight, with the earlier downpour, the temple looked even prettier!

Temple mistress was lovely. Went in for a juju-refresh and came out a new born calf. In all seriousness I think might be my favourite temple, visually. love the open space and helpful numbered prompts for the different 'praying/altar-stations' for those not familiar with the order of convention. I will be back when my mind or spirit finds itself in need of divine comfort and wide-eyed respite.

九皇爷 temple. Most busy on 农历9月初一 till 初九which is dubbed the 九皇爷 birthday or festival .Have notes changing machine inside to buy joss sticks and put inside boxes. Also have praying sequence number and no of joss sticks to offer at each altar so just follow. Quite standard like most temples .
Temple built in 1919, one of the oldest temple dedicated to Nine-God Emperors. A very lively place during the lunar 9th month, and a serene place to pray during normal days.

Otherwise known as Hougang Dou Mu temple. Smallish taoist temple built in 1919 to honor the "9 emperors". Recently restored...and looks like new...which is kinda a problem. Check out photos for more details.
